Come Spend Your Day With Us!

Volunteers are an integral part of our food distribution and help bring our mission to life!  Whether you have a half day or a full day to spare, we could use and appreciate your help.

    Latest News

    WE'VE ACHIEVED THE HIGHEST LEVEL OF TRANSPARENCY

    Were committed to the highest level of transparency! Our organization earned a 2019 Platinum Seal of Transparency, showcasing the progress and results were making toward our mission! Check out our updated GuideStar #NonprofitProfile

    WE'RE PAINTING THE FOOD BANK

    Help us #PainttheBank by donating paint supplies to FARSB! Paint supplies will be used for our volunteer engagement renovation project-- a project in which our volunteers will be taking used pallets and painting them to create vibrant works of art for our volunteer center! Learn more HERE.

    WE'VE PARTNERED WITH TARGET CIRCLE

    Were participating in the Target Circle program! You can vote for us and help direct Targets giving
    to benefit our nonprofit. For full program details and
    restrictions click HERE.

    FARSB RECEIVES $100,000 FROM S. MARK TAPER FOUNDATION

    This grant will support programs such as those targeted to feed children in the Inland Empire, like FARSBs Kids Markets and School Pantries. 

    JOIN US FOR A FREE LUNCH!
    Join us on February 12, 2020 for a FREE soup-kitchen style community luncheon! Learn what your local food bank is doing to combat hunger, hear from a special guest speaker, and take a tour of our distribution center. RSVP HERE!
    NORMS DONATES 
    $4,000 TO FARSB

    NORMS Restaurant of Riverside donated $4,000 to FARSB as part of there #MakeCaringtheNorm campaign that took place this past September during Hunger Action Month.  FARSB is extremely thankful for their continued support.

    THE MILLION MEALS GALA

    Raise your glass and help us end hunger in the Inland Empire.  Our annual million meals gala is our largest fundraiser of the year.  Sign up here, for a memorable night and a chance to make a difference.

    OLDER NEWS

    Why Do You Give?

    Mary M.

    Community Donor

    I donate in the honor of the I.E.  where I've lived for 29 years and my children and grandchildren live now.

    Stephanie Otero

    CEO

    I believe in giving back and I choose FARSB because there are people in our community who need us & I know with confidence that 98% of my donation goes back into the community.

    I emailed last night about needing food for my family & I am so thankful you reached out and gave us food! You have no idea how much we needed this and how blessed we are for your help!  You guys are amazing!

    We don't have much to give, but we know how lucky we are to have enough.

    Feeding America has been such a Blessing to my family. To those that need guidance in these areas in their life, I recommend to contact Feeding America Riverside|San Bernardino.

    Anne D.
